textBeforeTable: ROOKIE OF THE WEEK Chiaka Ogbogu, Texas, Fr., MB, Coppell, Texas/Coppell Ogbogu recorded a .323 hitting percentage with an average of 2.50 kills last week as Texas swept conference opponents TCU and Oklahoma to start Big 12 play at 2-0. The freshman also recorded six blocks and averaged 3.08 points for the Longhorns. 2013 BIG 12 WEEKLY AWARDS Kristen Hahn, Iowa State, Sr., L, Cedar Rapids, Iowa/Kennedy Hahn was dominant in the Cyclones’ back-row during ISU’s three-set victory over Baylor on Saturday. The senior finished the match with 21 digs, for an average of 7.00 digs per set as Iowa State out-dug the Bears 57-44. Hahn’s digs were well spread out with six in the first set, eight in the second set and seven in the final frame. Her total of 21 was the third-best output in a three-match set in the Big 12 this season. She continues to lead the conference in digs, with a season average of 5.56. DEFENSIVE PLAYERS OF THE WEEK Caroline Jarmoc, Kansas, Sr., MB, Calgary, Alberta, Canada/Springbank Community Jarmoc blocked eight attacks against the Horned Frogs to lead the floor and help KU double up TCU in team blocks (10.0-5.0). Her performance propelled her to third in the league in blocks per set (1.31), and the eight blocks was the second-most in the Big 12 in a three-set match this season.
